Link to BLOG: https://windylandscollies.wordpress.com/blog/

NEWS

WINDY LANDS Z LITTER – Imamo mladičke ♥

Here there are – long awaited and already so loved – Lumi and Mike’s little ones, our Z litter

It is so wonderful to round up our first circle of the alphabet, starting with homegrown A litter of granny Sky and finishing it with granddaughter Lumi’s Z litter.

Puppies are beautiful, healthy and we are totally in love with them already

We are really enjoying these precious moments with mummy Lumi, who is just an amazing and devoted mum as her granny Sky was, and the 6 little treasures, with Lani being a loving puppy sitter and grandma

Pedigree:

Mum – Lumi (WL Quite Exquisite), my top winning bit*ch – PUPPY HOPE, MULTI JCH, MULTI CH, GRAND CH, CIB, TOP COLLIE 2022, daughter of VETERAN WORLD WINNER Beyond Limits of the Windy Lands

Dad – Mike (Vilkies Dvelkimas Magical Crystal), imported from Lithuania. He carries some really precious and unique lines in his pedigree, among them is 1 World winner and 2 European winners! He himself impressed with his big size (61 cm and super bone).

Both parents are beautiful, strong, sound and have wonderful, brave and loving temperaments!

More about the litter: https://windylands.eu/breeding_Z%20litter.htm

Puppies:

SPECIALITY SHOW ITALY WITH VALERIE GEDDES

We attended a truly wonderful and important event – Italian collie club 100s anniversary speciality show! The judge was the great Valerie Geddess, a collie breeder of 50+ years and in my eyes one of the biggest legends of collies world (kennel Ingleden). When I heard she would be judging I knew I needed to come to ask for her opinion of my collies! And it made me so happy listening to a wonderful description of my heart girl Lani (vet ww Beyond Limits of the Windy Lands) and winning BOS VETERAN in a line-up of truly quality and famous veteran females, BEST VETERAN and finally BIS VETERAN! There were 72 rough collies and 13 smooth collies entered! Winning that under such a renewed judge is just as important as winning world winner title with her! And most of all – we had the most fun in the ring together, Lani just loves showing herself!

There were two more collies that made me so proud at the speciality show yesterday – our gorgeous Gaia (multi CH Gaia Earth Goddess of the Windy Lands), who won a strong champion class, presented perfectly by her awesome owner Alberto Celestini. Watching their performance in the ring is real joy!

I also couldn’t be prouder of our super duo – Tilen and Nera (CH Belladona Windy Lingonskogen). It was only their third time together in a ring and they presented themselves like pros again! In a huge competition of 14 beautiful collie females, they were shortlisted among 6 best ones, who got excellent grade. Nera also got a truly beautiful description by the judge Valerie Geddess and that means the world to me. She has just turned two and is in her summer dress, so I am sure that is just a start for them:)

LANI – VETERAN WORLD WINNER!!!

My heart girl Lani – JCH, multi CH, CIB, multi vet CH, vet CIB, Top collie 23′ BEYOND LIMITS OF THE WINDY LANDS has just became VETERAN WORLD WINNER ’24 under the respectable judge Sean Delmar!

Wow wow wow

I decided to enter the show as it was in a nearby Zagreb and I saw it as a great opportunity to meet up with some friends from around the world and to see some of the collie legends in flesh. I only expected to go there and have some fun with my lovely Lani in the ring….and what a big surprise was winning a big and strong class of quality and famous veteran females and becoming vet WW!

My partner Tilen and Nera (CH Belladonna Windy Lingonskogen) did me so proud at the WDS as well! It was only their second time together in a ring and they were fantastic, giving a truly professional presentation, winning ex2 and RCC in a strong inter class under the judge Sean Delmar.

Biggest congrats also to her mum Tanna (CH Lunar Lakes Primadonna), who won ex3 in a huge open class, handled by my dear friend Sandra Cerjak .

More WDS results from Windy lands collies and their offspring:

Gaia’s (CH Gaia Earth Goddess of the Windy Lands) daughter Jill – Shirawood Karismatika is now PUPPY WORLD WINNER with puppy BOB! Gaia is a daughter of Lani’s sister Tara, so we have a winning team – ‘auntie’ Lani veteran WW and little Jill puppy WW. Congrats Alberto Celestii!

Chloe’s daughter (Lani’s granddaughter) BPISS, Future Hope Of Europe’23, DKJW’23, SEJW’23, KAUNAS WINTER JW’24, KIKA Cup Junior Winner’24, LT JCH, DKJCH Utopia Nova Awaited Allie was ex4 in a huge junior class out of 21 young females. Congrats Rebecca Nordahl.

Sandra Cerjak showed her handsome Damon, a son of our Mai (CH Marked by Moonlight of the Windy Lands) and was shortlisted in first 7 out of a huge group of young males.

Katarina Petrič (with my help) was showing her Diamons, a daughter of our Casper (CH WL Qnockout Dynamite) and she was shortlisted out of a really huge group of young females. Her brother Jack also got an excellent grade!

Kia Senicar and Aaron, the son of Kai (CH Bejewelled Sky of the Windy Lands) also did a lovely presentation and got an excellent grade.

Our smooth girl Stella (WL True Revolution with Icekeller), presented by her owner Katarina Malenšek, also got an excellent grade!

Biggest congrats to all the owners, you did me proud

WINDY LANDS Y LITTER

Windy Lands would like to present you our Y litter!

One month ago, on 23th March, 7 sweeties were born to our beautiful Melody and to Euro Winner ’21, Rocky. However, sadly, the litter was born 3 days too early (according to progesterone testing) and they were all incredibly small, from 90 to 180 gr. We lost 3 right away and we had 4 strong fighters. The smallest, Yvette, was fighting for 3 weeks and just when Denis and me thought we were out of the woods, she passed away in his arms. It was incredibly hard on us, and especially on Denis, who had been feeding her day and night, every 2 hours…so we needed a moment to grieve before we could post the story. Being a breeder can really be a hard and sad experience and in such moment, it is hard to gain strength to continue. I admire Denis, he had been through so many losses, but he always comes back, stronger and more dedicated!

So now we can present you the 3 fighters from our Y litter, who are now big, strong, healthy and incredibly adorable. At 4 weeks they are already very active, sweet and a little bit naughty. They will help us heal our broken hearts! Here are our strong boy Yosh and the two beautiful sisters, Yasmine and Yumi

NEW MILESTONE – WINDY LANDS HAS BECOME A FAMILY KENNEL / WINDY LANDS JE POSTALA DRUŽINSKA PSARNA

With 2024, my life partner, Tilen Vodlan, has joined us and has become an official co owner of our Windy Lands kennel. So from now on, we have a family breeding ♥

LANI IS TOP ROUGH COLLIE OF 2023

My heart girl Lani has had one hell of a show season, winning many BOB, BOG and BIS placings, putting her on top of Slovenian Rough collies as well as n#4 of all Slovenian herding breeds! She followed the success of her daughter Lumi, who was top rough collie of 2022 and n#2 adult rough collie of 2023 (being mostly shown abroad this year, which doesnt count as much for this competition)! I am so incredibly proud of my grils♥

THE QUEEN HAS LEFT US – RIP SKY ♥

29.10.2008 – 11.9.2023

‘If love alone could have saved you

you would have lived forever.’

I needed many weeks to be able to write this, and it still hurts beyond imagination…How can you put in words all the love you feel for a dog? How can you describe everything you have lived and experienced together? How can you put 15 years in a few sentences?

Sky is the reason my life took a completely different turn, she set me on a truly wonderful journey of breeding and showing, through her I have met so many wonderful new friends and fellow breeders, I have travelled all over Europe and beyond for shows, matings, puppy visits.. I have countless beautiful, wonderful, amazing memories with her that will keep her alive in my heart forever!

On one of her early shows, she was judged by Eva Eriksson and her words were: ‘You own a Star, she will be a Legend some day’. Sky was never a big show star (she gained a few champion titles and the judges really admired her beauty but she was much more of an agility, Frisbee, sheepdog dog), but she is a start of my incredible line of Windy Lands collies, all our litters go back to her Sky herself had 2 litters, our first two litters, and from them, Windy Lands collies have spread all around the world! She set a very high standard for me – I want her amazing, active, loving character, she was the smartest dog I have ever known! I hope she is passing on her incredible health – even on her deathbed at 15, her blood and organs were all still healthy and in great condition, but sadly, she suffered a stroke. And of course, her beauty – her colour, dignity and her expression were something out of a dream. She still visits me in my dreams and I am hoping she will continue to do so for a long time! I see so much of her in her granddaughter, my Lumi – she has her looks, her mimic, her character – and I am so grateful for that. Together with her mum Lani they are in a great consolation to me in this tragic period. Life will never be the same without our queen and pain will never truly go away, however I do try to focus and be grateful for all the happy years she has given us and the amazing legacy she left behind – my BLUE PEARL

‘You loved me without words

You hugged me without arms

You were there without it having to be earned

As long as by the end of the day I returned

You waited for me behind the door

Always happy to see me

As if I was someone you’d always adore

A bit of attention is all you ever asked for

And I’d gladly give you my affection

We had such a strong connection

And having you by my side

Always gave me a sense of protection

In you I could always confide

Lying next to me is how you replied

My hands petting your fur

In our own little bubble we were

Your cuddles were always the best

But now you reached a state of eternal rest

Not having you around anymore

Is leaving a big scar

And I don’t know where you are

But I will forever love you from afar.’

(anonymous)

RECOGNITION OF MY BREEDING

This year we are celebrating the 30th anniversary of our club – KLUB 1 and I was so happy and honoured to receive the diploma from our Club issued by Slovenian Cynological Association for my work as a breeder of rough collies. Last 12 years haven’t been easy, there have been many ups and downs, many tears shed and I even wanted to give up a few times, but the passion for the breed is so strong that it drives me forward despite the obstacles. I could never have done what I do without the support of some close friends who are there for me through thick and thin – you know who you are And of course, with the help of my many amazing co-breeders and my puppies’ owners. Thank you to our president Lidija Okleščen for seeing the value in my breeding and for all the advice at the beginning of my breeding career!

As a part of the celebration, my darling Lumi (CH Windy Lands Quite Exquisite) received the FCI group1 #5 Top dog award for 2022, being best rough collie of last year. This means so much to me as I absolutely love flying in the ring with her! When I started with her granny Sky 15 years ago, it was not an easy start – I was young, inexperienced and not very self-confident and it really wasn’t simple for the two of us. But in the last 12 years of my breeding, we have made over 30 champions and I am very proud that we always handle our dogs ourselves. I have grown so much as a person in these years and I am really happy I can live my dream with my collies and with all the wonderful friends I have met along the way!

SPRING SHOW SUCCESS

After a little break, our wonderful Neel came back in a ring with a bang yesterday! He not only won CC, CACIB, BEST MALE and BOB at IDS Varaždin in a strong competition, under Colombian judge Juan Alberto Grillo Londono, but he also finished his INTERNATIONAL CHAMPIONSHIP!

I adore this big teddy bear, he is the kindest, gentlest and most loving boy who is also bomb proof – a character you can only wish in a collie. I adore his size (61 cm) and bone, he has the dreamiest blue colour that shines from afar, and he passes it on onto his offsprings. He has sired three wonderful litters (at Aljaž Tratnik, Slovenia, at Sandra Cerjak – Darsanian, Croatia and at Joanne Kirisits, Austria https://windylands.eu/Neel-offsprings.htm ) and I am hoping he can have some more, before he becomes too old.

Neel has been very successful at shows and he can be proud of his many ch titles:

DANISH JCH, DANISH JUNIOR CLUB WINNER, DANISH CH, SLOVENIAN CH, BOSNIAN CH, CROATIAN CH, INTERNATIONAL CH. He is also multi CACIB and BOB winner.

In June we had a very special weekend in Umag, Croatia. For the first time, I showed my two heart girls together – mum Lani and her daughter Lumi! What a sweet experience! Lumi both days and today also her mummy joined us. Both girls showed trully wonderfully for me, flying in a ring and standing like real pros!

Lumi won 2 EX1, 2 CC AND 2 rCACIBS, that’s her 3rd CC in a row and she now only needs one more CC to finish also her Croatian CH.

Lani was shown in a veteran class for the first time and the judge was impressed by her beauty, great condition and flawless movement. She won BOS VETERAN, VETERAN CACIB, BOB VETERAN and was shortlisted in BIS veteran out of a really numerous group of Veterans.

Thank you to the Italian judges CLAUDIO DE GIULIANI and ALESSANDRO ZEPPI for truly beautiful critiques of my girls!

A LITTER 11th BIRTHDAY – 11 YEARS OF WINDY LANDS

Happy 11th birthday to our A litter, my very first litter

Happy birthday in heaven to my miracle babygirl Lia, who left us last year. Still a day does not go by without me thinking about her and missing her but I am also grateful for the 10 years together that we had against all odds with Lia being born so small and with so many health issues. My first litter was a big struggle and I wasn’t sure I wanted to continue being a breeder….but then I found strength I am now very happy that I continued this path. It’s not easy and there have been a lot of heartbreaks and tears, but also many wonderful, happy moments and so many fantastic people met over the years!

The rest of the litter are all still going strong and are all loved by their families. Damon is enjoying his retirement in Finland, after siring 21 litters (one of them is a smooth one) and achieving many ch titles and important show wins.

Mei, the mum of our C and E litters, is also loving her retirement at our coast, spending a lot of time by the beach. My co-breeder Denis is continuing her line with his part of Windy Lands team! Also Mei was a very successful representative of this litter at shows, winning a few ch titles.

Our boys, Tai and Messi, have lived in loving pet homes all their lives and are still adored and wonderfully taken care by their families. Messi has become an older brother to his 2 legged sibling, who he adores

My dear babies, your mum Sky and me wish you many more healthy years, we both love you very much!

OUR QUEEN IS 14 YEARS OLD ♥

Sky

I am so grateful she is still with us, beautiful as ever and still healthy and fit!

This whole adventure started with her 14 years ago…the world of shows and breeding, now also dog training and grooming. She changed my life for the better and helped me find my purpuse!

She has formed an amazing line through her many many offsprings in Slovenia and around the world. I am so happy to see the photos of her kids, grandkids, greatgrandkids…

Sky herself is enjoying her retirenment in our home, loved and adored by us all. She gets many cuddles, daily walks, treats and she still loooves her food We are hoping we have quite a few more healthy years ahead of us! She is the guardian and best friend of her daughter Lani and great daughter Lumi, who reminds me a lot of Sky. I am truly blessed to have this amazing girl in my life!

Happy birthday my wonderful Blue Pearl!

Our Lumi (Windy Lands Quite Exquisite) rocked the show ring again! She impressed an UK judge Nick Smith, who I admire greatly, at our Speciality show for Fci1 and won against some very quality dogs and famous handlers. She became club winner ’22 and also won BEST OF BREED (her 6th one!)

The co breeder Denis and myself will need a little break from breeding after that:’

Her sister Chloe (WL Quarantine Bliss) was shown in Sweden two times, winning 2 CCs and two times BEST BITCH and BOS! She was also hip tested, just like her Swedish brother Caleb Quim and both have healthy, AA hips! That makes the whole Q litter healthy for hips! ♥

Despite being pretty much naked, she won CC, CACIB and BEST OF BREED (her 5th one) under a very friendly judge Tadej Nagode. Her nephew Rocky (WL Rather Magnificent) won a CC and BOS and little niece Tillie (WL Thrilling News with Icekeller) won puppy BOB and finished slo puppy hope title.

Lingonskogen B litter with Windy Lands

I am very happy to present you this wonderful litter, bred by my dear friend Kia Seničar, kennel Lingonskogen, in collaboration with Windy Lands.

When Kia was searching for a new show-breeding female, I suggested her Lunar Lakes litter, as they were having puppies from Big Ben, the dog I have been admiring ever since I saw him win eu junior title in Slovenia, over 10 years ago. Tanna has proven herself to be not only beautiful, but a wonderful, loving companion and a successful showgirl. Later, Kia and I searched for a male that would complete Tanna and we went on a trip to Tuscany together to have a date with the handsome Tom – Beldones Tom Wood, a dog who does not charm only with his beautiful looks but also with his loving and charming nature. Thank you dear Roberto for entrusting him to us! And kennel Beldones to send him to Italy, so we were able to use him.

We are more than thrilled with the result of this mating – we got 4 absolutely gorgeous puppies (3 boys and 1 girl). Born big, strong and lively at almost 400 grams! Later they moved at Windy Lands where they have had a very happy childhood:)

UNIQUE – U LITTER

Our princess is here – and she is perfect!

After a very difficult delivery that ended with the middle of the night emergency vet visit, our little blue jewel was born safely at the vet office (just minutes before they would start prepping mum for the cesarean). Having singletons comes with many complications (I surely have tons of experience with that) and we are so grateful we could welcome this precious baby safely into the world!

Welcome little Unique – Windy Lands Uniquely Dressed. My Lani’s first granddaughter and the 3rd generation of my wonderful blues! Her mum Lainie is a wonderful, calm and very loving mum. Together with family Krstinc they are taking a great care of the little one.

Thank you to Jozsef for giving us the beautiful Neon who shines with his amazing blue colour and for helping make this miracle possible. Little one seems to be a perfect mix of her wonderful parents and we are hoping she continues to grow healthily and brings her mum Lainie and her human family lots of joy!

WINDY GIRLS

I am so blessed to be able to share my life with these three gorgeous collie girls – granny Sky, who has taught me so much about life and with whom this whole journey started She has given me two wonderful litters and with that a very strong, beautiful and precious line. Sky is the smartest collie I know and she is still going strong at 13,5!

Her daughter Lani, my heart dog who absolutely adores me and with whom we’ve had many many wonderful adventures together so far. She has been very succesful at shows and helped me start loving them and to recover from my shows ‘stage fright’ and has given me three very precious litters She is now retired from the whelping box but we shall hit the how ring again soon

And our youngest one, the granddaughter Lumi, our new show star, the most loving and gentle collie I know! Everything we do together is pure joy! She is proving to be my second heart dog – I am forming a very strong bond with her as well and falling in love with her deeper every day! I am so happy I decided to keep her last year – just like her mum Lani, she wasn’t planned, but was destined to share her life with me

We all still miss our little black beauty Lia, we feel she is looking over us from doggy heaven

REVOLUTIONARY T LITTER

Easter bunny has brough us an early Easter present – 6 little ‘bunnies’ from our T litter! This time we decided to do something special and experimental and we mated our Aida with a wonderful smooth collie Tin Tin.

What was our goal? To widen the genetic diversity of Windy Lands line and to implement some qualities Tin Tin’s line has – the big size, fantastic character, excellent tail carriage, body, movement and to get the cea free gene from a different line.

We are thrilled with the result – we got 6 extremely strong, vivid and lively puppies (almost 400 gr each). We have 2 blue girls, 3 tricolour girls and one very beautiful blue prince. Their daddy Tin Tin carries the rough gene so all the pups might be rough collies, all are genetically cea carriers and dm non carriers.

This litter is made in collaboration with Aida’s owner Aljaž Tratnik and his partner Barbara Potočnik (kennel Icekeller). Thank you guys for believing in this match and taking a great care of the babies! And thanks to to Tin Tin’s owner Nina Zubrinic for all the help and support. Thank you also to our breeding comitee for allowing this to happen – it is first such litter in Slovenia. It will be very exciting watching them grow!

GOODBYE MY MIRACLE GIRL LIA ♥

It’s so hard to find words to write this

My little Lia, our miracle girl, closed her eyes forever last Friday. I needed a little time for myself before I was able to post this. She left us so suddenly and unexpectedly! She was fine on Thursday and fell asleep in my arms on Friday, surrounded also by my sisters Ana and Jasna. Both were there, helping me save her 10 years ago, when she was a tiny fragile baby and they were there for me and her also now, when her life journey came to an end.

Our fierce fighter Lia fought all the obstacles life threw at her bravely and with a smile on her face until the very last day. She really knew how to enjoy live and every single day she was showing me how grateful she was to me for giving her a chance when she was a tiny tiny little babygirl.Lia was from my very first litter, when I was still a very young breeder. She was born miniature and not fully developed, so we had to tube feed her and later do a few operations to enable her to have a normal life. Due to all complications, she stayed quite little and puppy-like. When she was 2, she was run over by a car and her lungs collapsed..it was another little miracle she survived that against all odds! She really had the strongest will to live! She had some issues with environmental allergies (as her immune system was compromised, not receiving any colostrum at birth), but we later found solutions in more natural ways of living and feeding and she lived a happy and quality life! At a start no vet could ever imagine this poor tiny baby would live for long, but she would celebrate her tenth birthday in a month!

From the breeding point of view, it wasn’t the smartest thing to do, keeping her, as she was ‘taking a space’ of some healthy girl who I could breed with…but Lia was our beloved family member, my parent’s favourite one and she had a very special and dear place in my heart and we shared such a strong bond. If I wanted to keep her and also continue breeding, I had to find other ways. So now I mostly have collies in co-ownerships. Thanks to Lia, I managed to build a wide network of Windy Lands collies with my wonderful co-breeders! And Lia was an amazing puppy sitter to all the puppies born here, she stayed very puppy like also in her character and always loved to play with her little friends

We are heartbroken and miss her terribly, but we are also grateful for the ten years we got to have this amazing, sweet and strong baby girl in our life. She will live on in our hearts and in many many beautiful memories we’ve made in these years together

Run free, healthy and young again over the Rainbow, our miracle girl!

SKY’s 12th BIRTHDAY

Today is a very special day – our QUEEN Sky is celebrating her 12th birthday!12 years ago, after loosing my first collie Gaja, I was looking for a companion and a potential agility partner. I didn’t want to change the breed because collies are just irreplaceable, but I did want to change the colour, so the new puppy would mean a fresh start and help me overcome my sadness over loosing Gaja. I didn’t plan shows and breeding and we did star with training agility, Frisbee, obedience and sheepdogs as Sky is a truly smart collie. But since she was also incredibly pretty, we tried a few shows and I was hooked:) Sky has achieved quite a few champions titles in her life and she has given me two most amazing litter, our A and B litters. She is now a mother, granny, great granny and great great granny to many wonderful collies all around the world. She still loves to catch ball and going on walks with us. She always warmly welcomes all the puppies that grow up at Windy Lands and is still a great mother to her two daughters Lia and Lani, who live with us.I am hoping there are still many healthy years in front of us! Elder dogs are so special, there is a unique sweetness and gentleness in them! I love you to the moon and back, my wonderful girl

ANOTHER SAD EXPERIENCE:(

We mated our sweet Pai with an outstanding young boy Ziggy. But sadly, our Pai was carrying just one puppy! We tried importing chilled semen for the first time in my breeding career and everything worked out great – Pai is very fertile, having a big litter last year, Ziggy sired 10 puppies in his latest litter, the semen arrived in excellent quality and I am very grateful to Ziggy’s owner Cathy Sonntag for all the help with this plan as well as Pai’c co-owners for monitoring progesterone carefully and taking her to our best repro vet. There was just one obstacle – Fedex delivered the semen 1 day too late due to some strike in France! So when we finally got the semen, it was already 5 days after the ovulation for Pai and the result was just one puppy. As it usually happens with just one baby, Pai didn’t start the labour on her own and cesarian was needed. Sadly, we lost our puppy boy during the operation. To say we are heartbroken is an understatement. Breeding is really hard and it has been especially difficult for us in the last few months. We really hope sun will start shining soon for us as it’s been a very dark season for so long now:(
